column7: Yesterday with the advanced group in Cerro Mariposa, we played Jeopardy, with categories including Calvin & Hobbes, in which you had to explain the joke of a Calvin & Hobbes comic strip; Surf; Teacher Trivia; Translations; Tongue Twisters; and Question Words. Defying the confines of their name, Team "i don't know" took an early lead, but in the end Team "eh." caught up and the game ended in a tie, 5100-5100.   //   Ayer con el grupo avanzado de Cerro Mariposas jugamos Jeopardy, con las siguientes categorias: Calvin & Hobbes, en la que hab√≠a que explicar la broma en un c√≥mic de Calvin & Hobbes; Surf; Datos Curiosos de las T√≠as; Traducciones, Trabalenguas, y Palabras de Preguntas. Resistiendo los limites de su nombre, el equipo "i don't know" tom√≥ una temprana delantera, pero al final, el equipo "eh." remont√≥ y el partido termin√≥ empatado 5100-5100.

Recently, the Valpo Surf Project (VSP) was invited to send some of its students to participate in the Our Ocean Science Camp (put on by Fundaci√≥n Ciencia Joven) in Valpara√≠so. This camp was organized as a part of the Our Ocean Conference, and was designed to teach students who attend public schools and are in either the 5th or 6th grade about the conservation of the species and ecosystems that inhabit the sea. Read about their experience in our latest blog post! // Recientemente, Valpo Surf Project (VSP) fue invitado a participar del Campamento Cient√≠fico Nuestro Oc√©ano en Valpara√≠so. Esta actividad, organizada en el marco de la conferencia Nuestro Oc√©ano, estuvo dise√±ada para educar a estudiantes de 5to y 6to b√°sico, pertenecientes a escuelas p√∫blicas, sobre la conservaci√≥n de las especies y ecosistemas que habitan en el mar. column7:
On 16 September 2015, an 8.3 magnitude earthquake struck the coast of central Chile, triggering tsunami waves in certain cities. Although we are happy to report the safety of our team and students, the beach where we surf has suffered significant damage. Read more about the disaster in this week's blog. // El 16 de septiembre de 2015, un terremoto de magnitud 8.3 (Richter) golpe√≥ a la costa central de Chile, provocando alertas de tsunami y evacuaciones costeras. Aunque nuestro equipo, estudiantes y voluntarios se encuentran todos bien, nos encontramos muy afectados por el da√±o causado por olas del tsunami a la playa donde surfeamos cada semana. Lee m√°s sobre el desastre en la nueva publicaci√≥n del blog.
http://valposurfproject.com/after-the-tsunami-damage-to-local-beaches/

column7: New England friends of VSP, tickets are going fast to our Annual Boston Silent Auction Fundraiser! This Saturday, May 30th we invite you to the Impact Hub Boston to share an evening of great food, drinks, and company to support our program in Chile. Awesome auction items this year including prints from Ryan Struck Photography, Chris Burkard Photography, items from Artemis Design Co., and more! Food and beverages by Samuel Adams, Gosling's Rum, KEEL, Downeast Cider House, Flatbread Somerville, and Anna's Taqueria. Buy your tickets before they run out! Share the event through the facebook page and spread the word! http://www.eventbrite.com/e/valpo-surf-project-boston-2015-silent-auction-fundraiser-tickets-16412871340

column7:
Support the VSP Before the End of the Year at http://valposurfproject.com/donate-now/.

Your tax deductible gift will make a big difference for our students in 2015.  

We empower our students with the tools to better their own lives and positively impact their communities.  Your support is essential to help us shape leaders like Claudio, our first student who returned as a mentor to influence the VSP's next generation. Watch the video at https://vimeo.com/97902706 to hear his story and learn about the powerful impact your donation will have in our students‚Äô lives.

column7:
Last week VSP participated in the FICSURF CHILE - Festival Internacional de Cine de Surf in Santiago. Congratulations to all the organizations and films that were involved in this awesome event, Puertecillo Playas Libres, Punta de Lobos por Siempre, GiveSurf, Patagonia Chile, Sanuk Chile, Cerveza Corona Chile, Farias Moreno Photography.
Check out our latest blog post to read and see photos from the event. 
http://valposurfproject.com/ficsurf-international-surf-film-festival/

No se olviden a reservar las fechas 25-28 de noviembre para asistir al FICSURF CHILE - Festival Internacional de Cine de Surf en Centro Cultural Las Condes.  100% del dinero recaudado por las entradas beneficia a las ONGs invitadas.  Eligen a The Valpo Surf Project cuando compran sus entradas para destinar su aporte!  

Save the dates November 25-28 to attend FICSURF CHILE - Chile's International Surf Film Festival at Centro Cultural Las Condes.  100% of ticket sales benefit the NGOs partnered with the festival.  Choose Valpo Surf Project when buying tickets to support the organization!

column7:
Last Friday October 17, 2014, the Valpo Surf Project hosted its Sixth Annual NYC Silent Auction Fundraiser in Manhattan with more than 175 people in attendance, the event was VSP‚Äôs best attended and most successful fundraiser to date.  We would like to especially thank everyone who attended and our event sponsors including the Centre for Social Innovation NYC, Runa Clean Energy Drinks, Frava Naturally Caffeinated Juice, and Sierra Nevada Brewing Co. for contributing to such a successful event.

We‚Äôd also like to extend our thanks to all of the donors who contributed to the success of the silent auction, including surf photographers Ryan Struck, Chris Burkard, Donald Crisitellio, Ryan Mack, and  Andreea Waters; custom surfboards from Malwitz Custom Surfboards and Union Surfboards; surf gear and gift certificates from Patagonia Surf Bowery, Barewires Surf Shop, Jake‚Äôs Surf Shop, Lost Weekend NYC Surf, Saturdays Surf NYC, Evil Paradise, Rareform, Spellbinders Surf and Snow, Summer Love Surfing and Yoga and  Pigdog Surf Academy (Springlake); artists Brainstorm Print and Design, Billy Name, Jeff Armstrong, Lexie Smith, Artemis Design Co., Sarah Oliver Handbags, Ali Cherkis, Ann Marie Steuber,  Lizzie Meltzer, Virgina Lunt; and local businesses Chelsea Williams Sonoma, Feel Food, DASH, Beach Haus Beer Co., Brooklyn Boulders, Bucketfeet, Carton Brewing Co., Manhattan Plaza Health Club, Ovest Pizzoteca, Rad Cakes Apparel,Shake Shack, Spitzer‚Äôs Corner, The Eddie‚Äôs Pizza Truck, Totto, The Eddie‚Äôs Pizza Truck, Georgette Keenan of Necessities for the Heart, Chronicle Books, Scholastic Books,  Yogamaya, and YogaWorks.  

This event could not have been possible without the support of the entire VSP staff, and our NYC event organizing committee including event coordinator Sam Rigby, VSP Global board of directors member Ryan Holbrook, and event committee members Nick Napolitano, Jenna Barzelay, Manuela Odell, Jennifer McInnis, James Lunt, Patrick Flaherty, Dean Thompson, Mark Thompson, Basil Henning, and Sara Hames; and our amazing volunteer staff including bar tender extraordinaires Michael Hansen and Alexandre Bacon and event photographer Caitlyn Warakomski.  

_______________________________

  
El viernes pasado 17 de octubre 2014, Valpo Surf Project se llev√≥ a cabo su Sexto Evento Anual de Recaudar Fondos en NYC en Manhattan; asistido por mas que 175 personas, fue el evento m√°s exitoso de la historia de VSP.  Queremos agradecer todas las personas que asistieron y los auspiciadores del evento incluyendo Centre for Social Innovation NYC, Runa Clean Energy Drinks, Frava Naturally Caffeinated Juice, y Sierra Nevada Brewing Co. por contribuir a un evento tan exitoso.

Tambi√©n nos gustar√≠a agradecer todos los donantes que contribuyeron al remate incluyendo fot√≥grafos de surf Ryan Struck, Chris Burkard, Donald Crisitellio, Ryan Mack, y  Andreea Waters; tablas de surf a medida por Malwitz Custom Surfboards y Union Surfboards; equipo de surf y certificados de Patagonia Surf Bowery, Barewires Surf Shop, Jake‚Äôs Surf Shop, Lost Weekend NYC Surf, Saturdays Surf NYC, Evil Paradise, Rareform, Spellbinders Surf and Snow, Summer Love Surfing and Yoga and  Pigdog Surf Academy (Springlake); artistas Brainstorm Print and Design, Billy Name, Jeff Armstrong, Lexie Smith, Artemis Design Co., Sarah Oliver Handbags, Ali Cherkis, Ann Marie Steuber,  Lizzie Meltzer, Virgina Lunt; y negocios locales Chelsea Williams Sonoma, Feel Food, DASH, Beach Haus Beer Co., Brooklyn Boulders, Bucketfeet, Carton Brewing Co., Manhattan Plaza Health Club, Ovest Pizzoteca, Rad Cakes Apparel,Shake Shack, Spitzer‚Äôs Corner, The Eddie‚Äôs Pizza Truck, Totto, The Eddie‚Äôs Pizza Truck, Georgette Keenan de Necessities for the Heart, Chronicle Books, Scholastic Books,  Yogamaya, y YogaWorks.  

This event could not have been possible without the support of the entire VSP staff, and our NYC event organizing committee including event coordinator Este evento no habr√≠a sido posible sin el apoyo del staff administrativo del VSP, y el comit√© del evento de NYC incluyendo el coordinador del evento Sam Rigby, miembro del directorio de VSP Global y miembros del comit√© del evento Nick Napolitano, Jenna Barzelay, Manuela Odell, Jennifer McInnis, James Lunt, Patrick Flaherty, Dean Thompson, Mark Thompson, Basil Henning, y Sara Hames; y nuestro equipo de voluntarios incluyendo los bartenders Michael Hansen y Alexandre Bacon y fot√≥grafa Caitlyn Warakomski.

Join the VSP tonight at Impact Hub Bay Area for our Silent Auction Fundraiser. Get your ticket before 5pm here: http://www.eventbrite.com/e/valpo-surf-project-2014-san-francisco-silent-auction-event-tickets-12037585743

Impact Hub Bay Area is located at 901 Mission St. San Francisco, CA. Support a great cause during an evening full of food, drinks, and bidding on a variety of great silent auction items from local artists and businesses. 

Tickets are $25 in advance or $35 at the door.

Be sure to bring card or cash for silent auction purchases!

No need to bring paper copy of ticket, once tickets are purchased, your name will be placed on a guest list at the door. Hope to see you there!

column7:
Come join members of the The Valpo Surf Project team on Friday, July 11 from 7-10 PM at Impact Hub Bay Area located at 901 Mission St. San Francisco, CA, for an evening of food, drinks, and bidding on a variety of great silent auction items from local artists and businesses. 

The event consists of an open bar courtesy of Sailor Jerry Rum and Magnolia Gastropub & Brewery, as well as hors d'oeuvres provided by The Little Chihuahua Mexican Restaurant and Sabores del Sur

Silent Auction items donated from Anderson Surfboards, Proof Lab Surf Shop, Brainstorm Print and Design, 21st Amendment Brewery, Chris Burkard Photography, Chronicle Books, Tacolicious, RareForm, Yoga Tree, Mission Cliffs Indoor Rock Climbing Gym, Planet Granite San Francisco, Taylor Stitch, Park District Coffee Co., Patagonia San Francisco, Whole Foods Market, Franklin and many more. 
        
Tickets are $25 in advance or $35 at the door.
Purchase here: http://www.eventbrite.com/e/valpo-surf-project-2014-san-francisco-silent-auction-event-tickets-12037585743

Be sure to bring card or cash for silent auction purchases!

No need to bring paper copy of ticket, once tickets are purchased, your name will be placed on a guest list at the door. Hope to see you there!

column7:
Come join members of the The Valpo Surf Project team on Friday, July 11 from 7-10 PM at Impact Hub Bay Area, located at 901 Mission St. San Francisco, CA, for an evening of food, drinks, and bidding on a variety of great silent auction items from local artists and businesses. 

The event consists of an open bar courtesy of Sailor Jerry Rum and Magnolia Gastropub & Brewery, as well as hors d'oeuvres provided by The Little Chihuahua Mexican Restaurant and Sabores del Sur.

Tickets are $25 in advance or $35 at the door.
Purchase here: http://www.eventbrite.com/e/valpo-surf-project-2014-san-francisco-silent-auction-event-tickets-12037585743

Be sure to bring card or cash for silent auction purchases!

No need to bring paper copy of ticket, once tickets are purchased, your name will be placed on a guest list at the door.

This #weekend, VSP students got to try for the first time climbing & bouldering at Tornamesa Centro de Escalada the #local rock #gym. With boundless energy, our students were up and down the walls like naturals.
~~~~~~
Este fin de semana, los alumnos del VSP fueron para la primera vez al Tornamesa Centro de Escalada, el gimnasio local de escalar, a tratar un deporte nuevo. Con tanta energ√≠a, los chicos estuvieron como escaladores naturales! 

Muchas gracias a Tornamesa por todo la ayuda y el espacio de taller.

NGO Surf Program Looking for Intern Applicants! Deadline approaching! 

Interested in the surf? Working with kids? Taking care of our environment? Want to step outside your comfort zone & make a true difference? The Valpo Surf Project is looking for several-self motivated interns to join the team in Valpara√≠so, Chile for 12 months, working to educate and mentor the youth of the city.

Fill out an application before the June 30th deadline. Read here for full details and information.

Since the wildfires happened in Valparaiso in April, the VSP has been diligently working to reconstruct a home in Cerro Litre with a team of two architects and many volunteers. Check out the newest blog post for updates on the Olson Family House and the impressive progress the Valpo Surf Project has made.
~~~~~~~~~
Desde abril, cuando pasaron los incendios en Valpara√≠so, el VSP ha estado trabajando diligentemente para reconstruir una casa en Cerro Litre con un equipo de dos arquitectos y muchos voluntarios. Mira el nuevo post de blog para m√°s informaci√≥n sobre La Casa de Familia Olson y el impresionante progreso que ha hecho el Valpo Surf Project.

http://valposurfproject.com/fuerza-valparaiso-update-on-the-olson-family-house/

column7:
NGO Surf Program Looking for Intern Applicants! Deadline approaching! 

Interested in the surf? Working with kids? Taking care of our environment? Want to step outside your comfort zone & make a true difference? The Valpo Surf Project is looking for several-self motivated interns to join the team in Valpara√≠so, Chile for 12 months, working to educate and mentor the youth of the city.
 
Fill out an application before the June 30th deadline. Read here for full details and information.
http://www.idealist.org/view/internship/kpHfN7h4TbfP/

column7:
On May 31, 2014 Valpo Surf Project hosted its most successful and best attended fundraiser to date at Impact Hub Boston with sponsorship from Downeast Cider House, Gosling's Rum, Sierra Nevada, Flatbread Somerville and Anna's Taqueria.

With more than 165 people in attendance, the event was a great opportunity to raise funds and awareness for the Valpo Surf Project‚Äôs programming, and to premier a recent documentary about Claudio, our first student with the Valpo Surf Project who has recently become a junior surf instructor and mentor with the VSP.

A huge contribution to the event‚Äôs success was through donations of silent auction items from local businesses such as Chino Surf boards, Brooklyn Boulders Somerville, The Institute of Contemporary Art/Boston, Cuppow, Jiberish, Vans, Taza Chocolate, Cambridge Naturals, Porter Square Books, b.good, Boston Sports Club, ACK Surf School, Tenoch Mexican, Camp Waziyatah, Pretty Things Beer & Ale Project, Mary Tiseo, George Pillsbury, and Pepita Soto. The silent auction also showcased work from Pescadotes, Brainstorm, Chris Burkard Photography, Clarkography, Ryan Struck Photography, and local artists Albie Davis, Pat Falco, Erik Heumiller, Jeff Armstrong, and Coastal Creations by the Maine Milk Maiden.

Thank you so much to everyone who made this event such a success, including Impact Hub Boston, all of our food and beverage sponsors, silent auction donors, all of the guests who attended, production company Herman Mantis for photo and video assistance.

The VSP team would like to specifically thank all of the volunteers who contributed to the planning and execution of the event, particularly our event coordinator Amanda Pillsbury and our volunteer team including Kait Barlow, Nina Berg, Kate Brown, Brendan Buckland, Peter Griffith, Ned Rich, Paula Hernandez, Tallulah Knopp, Lily Kofke, Tom Meehan, Seth Myer, Nick Napolitano, Josie Reinhardt, Helen Sullivan, Pennie Taylor, Kristofer Tupper, and Amanda Vernon.  

Much thanks to our incredible intern team in Valpara√≠so of Natalie Valentin, Beatriz Bola√±os, and Max Eyes for their hard work in making the event a success and to Martha Rigby and Francisco Torres for their excellent job in directing and editing the Meet Claudio video.

column7:
Saludos Todos!

Si alguien le interesa, quiero avisarles que ma√±ana estamos juntando voluntarios a la Casa VSP a las 9:30am para ir a ayudar a una familia que conocemos. 

Si les gustar√≠a venir, por favor traigan con Uds: agua y comida para sus mismos para almorzar, bloqueador, zapatos firmes/duros, mascarillas, algo para proteger a los ojos y guantes. Si pueden, tambi√©n traigan palas, rastrillos, y bolsas de basura/cajas de cart√≥n. 

NO TRAIGAN objetos personales de valor (c√°maras, dinero, iphones, etc) porque desafortunadamente todav√≠a hay algunas personas aprovechando.

Tambi√©n pueden compartir esta informaci√≥n si tienen amigos interesados. Much√≠simas gracias y un abrazo enorme a todos. Cualquier consulta o duda, nos avisen por Face o el celular del equipo: 56515052. ¬°Fuerza Valpo!

column7: Residents of Santiago/Valpo, for those who want to help out, The Valpo Surf Project is organizing relief efforts:

column2: {u'paging': {u'cursors': {u'after': u'WTI5dGJXVnVkRjlqZFhKemIzSTZNVEF4TlRJek1qWTBORE00TURjME1ETTZNekV3TnpVMU1ETT0=', u'before': u'WTI5dGJXVnVkRjlqZFhKemIzSTZNVEF4TlRJek1qTTJORGcyTXpJME1ETTZNekV3TmpFME1qVT0='}}, u'data': [{u'message': u'Be safe you guys.', u'from': {u'name': u'Peter Marsters', u'id': u'836131014727'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31061425'}, {u'message': u'Cu√≠dense!', u'from': {u'name': u'Loretto Serrano Uma\xf1a', u'id': u'10203269866362063'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31062417'}, {u'message': u'Please send me a message with a full contact name: First, Middle, Last Name where I can send an Electronic Wire Transfer. I have family in Cerro Playa Ancha and I'd love to help.', u'from': {u'name': u'Moises Alvarez', u'id': u'614918775280227'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31062433'}, {u'message': u'Take care of each other... Thinking of you all!!', u'from': {u'name': u'Ella Farnsworth', u'id': u'779704987941'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31063371'}, {u'message': u'Just heard about the fire. Glad to hear you guys are ok. If we want to send supplies where do we send them?', u'from': {u'name': u'Jim Hayes', u'id': u'10203625485531955'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31067829'}, {u'message': u'Se  puede hacer llegar a traves de cruz roja?', u'from': {u'name': u'Ofelia Moreno', u'id': u'696029983827524'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31069439'}, {u'message': u'Jim, I'm heading back to Chile on Wednesday---I've been in the US for my sister's wedding.  If you guys have school supplies and/or toiletries that you'd like to donate, I'm going to fill an extra bag with materials to bring down.  My number is 908-216-7056, I can swing by to pick stuff up.', u'from': {u'name': u'Jon Steuber', u'id': u'786163120787'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31075125'}, {u'message': u'I will definitely put some stuff together for you guys. And I'm working in Princeton so you can swing by there if you want', u'from': {u'name': u'Jim Hayes', u'id': u'10203625485531955'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31075193'}, {u'message': u'Anything specific in terms of toiletries that you need Jon Steuber', u'from': {u'name': u'Jim Hayes', u'id': u'10203625485531955'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31075212'}, {u'message': u'Hey Jim, based on what the collection points around Valpo are asking for, the most needed toiletries are things like: toothbrushes and toothpaste, feminine products (pads, tampons), soap, and wet wipes/moist towelette type things. Also, everyone has stopped collecting clothes except for NEW underwear.', u'from': {u'name': u'Martha Rigby', u'id': u'10203103687336182'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31075283'}, {u'message': u'Also, Jim, I think that diapers might be a good space/weight ratio for something to bring down since I'll have about 50 pounds allotted in my other checked bag.', u'from': {u'name': u'Jon Steuber', u'id': u'786163120787'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31075309'}, {u'message': u'Hey Moises, I'll send you a private message.  Make sure to check your "Other Messages" folder where it will probably end up since we aren't facebook friends.', u'from': {u'name': u'Jon Steuber', u'id': u'786163120787'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31075334'}, {u'message': u'Jon thanks for the response. I'm in Los Angeles, Ca aside from a wire transfer I'd be more than happy to gather some toiletries and other supplies for you and Mail it via DHL. I know there's a DHL office there in Valpo. My family in Valpo is ok. I was just there last month and anything I can do for you guys if be more than happy.', u'from': {u'name': u'Moises Alvarez', u'id': u'614918775280227'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31075453'}, {u'message': u'Jon I'd also like to send some face masks for volunteers assisting in the impact zones along with Kevlar lined gloves. Based on photos I've seen the masks are not doing much to filter the dirt and smoke they are coming in contact with. The gloves also don't appear that good. Get me a list please. I've friend requested you and just waiting on your message. Thanks', u'from': {u'name': u'Moises Alvarez', u'id': u'614918775280227'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31075503'}], u'summary': {u'total_count': 14, u'order': u'chronological'}}

Hello everyone. Please DO NOT bring food or clothes. What we need the most is the following:
-building materials (shovels, wheelbarrows, nails, gloves, etc.)
-toiletries
-water
-school supplies
Thank you everyone. Soon we are going to make a plan to mobilize and help to rebuild that which has been burned. We are here at the Casa VSP at Garibaldi 105 in Cerro La Cruz. Strength to Valpo!

Hola a todos y todas, esperamos que est√°n a salvo. Estamos ac√° en la Casa VSP listos a aceptar donaciones de cualquier cosa para ayudar las v√≠ctimas del incendio de anoche. Por favor traigan comida, agua, ropa, pa√±ales, guantes para sacar escombros, etc.
La Casa VSP ubica en Garibaldi 105, Cerro La Cruz. De la intersecci√≥n Colon con Francia, sigue arriba por Francia y gira a la izquierda en Vallejos. La primera calle que se encuentra ser√° Garibaldi, gira a la izquierda y estamos en la casa 105.
Qu√©dense atentos hoy y en los pr√≥ximos d√≠as. Estamos averiguando como podemos ayudar en la mejor manera posible; pronto vamos a organizar un grupo de voluntarios. 
___________________________________________________
Hello everyone, we hope you are all safe. We are here in the Casa VSP, ready to accept donations for victims of the fire last night. Please bring food, water, clothes, diapers, work gloves to remove rubble, etc.
The Casa VSP is located on 105 Garibaldi in Cerro La Cruz. From the intersection of Colon and Francia, continue towards the hills on Francia and turn left on Vallejos. The first street you see will be Garibaldi. Turn left there and we are in house number 105.
Stay tuned today and the next few days. We are figuring out how we can help in the best way possible; soon we will organize a group of volunteers.

Hey everyone! We did an outstanding job during our Saturday beach clean at Playa Portales...With 70 volunteers, we cleaned 75 big bags worth of garbage: 1,305 pounds of trash, of which 357 pounds were recyclable plastic & glass. Thanks to everyone who came and showed support!

#UxAL #UnidosPorAguasLimpias Save The Waves

column7:
Hey everyone, in just over a week the VSP will have it's first beach clean of the year at Playa Portales.  This event is part of Unidos Por Aguas Limpias, where costal beach cleans will happen across the country to encourage a clean environment & conscientious community!

When: Saturday, March 22 10:00-14:00
Where: Playa Diego Portales, southern side of Caleta Portales
 
~~~~~~~

Saludos a todos! En poco m√°s de una semana, el VSP colabor√° en la primera limpieza de playa del a√±o en Playa Portales. El evento es parte de Unidos Por Aguas Limpias, en que limpiezas costales pasar√°n sobre todo el pa√≠s a fomentar un ambiente limpio y una comunidad consciente. ¬°Fuerza Chile!

Cuando: Sabado, el 22 de marzo, 10:00-14:00
Donde: Playa Portales, lado sure√±o de Caleta Portales

Save The Waves

Here VSP is featured on Discovery Sports, Latin America's Discovery Channel page. A shout out to our friend, the author, Juan Manuel Daza who wrote the article after a visit Casa VSP. He even took to the sea with us and worked alongside our students! Give it a read it!

column7:
Hey everyone! What a week we've had teaching surf lessons at La Boca! Due to a northwest swell, the waves have been wild and here, our students from Cerro Toro are ready for more! And where would we be without our JAC Chile and Derco VSP van?! 
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Saludos a todos! Que semana incre√≠ble que hemos tenido ense√±ando lecciones de surf en La Boca! Por la marejada noroeste, las olas han sido locas! Y aqu√≠ nuestros estudiantes de Cerro Toro est√°n listos para m√°s! Donde estar√≠amos sin el caravan de JAC Chile y Derco! Gracias!

column7: We are very proud of our student, Nikolas Corvalan, who is leaving tomorrow to begin his career in the Chilean Navy. Nik has been a role model for our younger students in and out of the classroom. We will miss Nikolas, but we are excited to see what the future holds for this young man. Although he is leaving Valparaiso he will always be a part of the @valposurfproject family.     / / /    Estamos muy orgullos de nuestro alumno, Nikolas Corvalan, qui√©n se va a empezar su carrera con la armada ma√±ana. Nik ha sido un ejemplo para seguir. Le vamos a echar de menos y le deseamos lo mejor en todo. Aunque se va de Valpara√≠so siempre va a ser parte de la familia VSP.

Here's a photo from the first week of surf sessions at Playa La Boca in ConCon! Say hello to our new students from Cerro Toro. Wicked thankful to have our new JAC Chile and Derco sponsored van‚Äîto the beach & back!

We're almost there!  The support this holiday season has been incredible!  We're currently $1,600 away from meeting our $15,000 goal for expansion in 2014.  

Every donation has an important impact on our students.  Please check out our annual appeal letter at http://us2.campaign-archive2.com/?u=1fb786b7dff8dae3d5c570968&id=a8c624a902 to see how your donation will impact the program and consider donating before the new year!

column7:
We are looking for smart, creative, self-starting young people to serve as interns and help take the VSP to another level. 

Interns will gain valuable experience, have a voice and an impact in a small but growing non-profit, have an amazing time in an amazing country, and most of all, help out a group of kids who really need it. Applications for a July 2014 start date are due by December 31.

More info at: http://valposurfproject.com/1160-2/ 

Please share and help get the word out!

The VSP is again accepting applications for its year-long internship program for internships beginning in JULY 2014!  We‚Äôre looking for motivated and enthusiastic young people to help this growing organization and to get involved with many different aspects of our operations, including teaching and program logistics, development and strategy, and marketing communications.

Vengan a asistir al FICSURF CHILE - Festival Internacional de Cine de Surf, el 28-30 de Noviembre en la Corporaci√≥n Cultural Las Condes, en Santiago.  The Valpo Surf Project ha sido elegido como una organizaci√≥n beneficiaria del evento y despu√©s de comprar su entrada, pueden donar 100% del valor de la entrada a nuestro programa! column7:
On Saturday, October 19, the Valpo Surf Project hosted its 5th Annual NYC Silent Auction Fundraiser at the Centre for Social Innovation in Manhattan. The event was our most successful fundraiser to date, with more than 125 people in attendance and generous support from our presenting sponsors Ketel One, Kona Brewing Company, and Runa Clean Energy, helping to raise funds to carry out our mission using surfing as a tool to engage inner city youth in Valpara√≠so, Chile.

The event attendants enjoyed an evening of food, drinks, and casting bids on an array of great gear and prizes available for silent auction. We‚Äôd like to thank the silent auction contributors for their generous support for making this event such a success. A huge thanks to surfboard shapers Monroe Surf Co. and  Malwitz Custom Surfboards, surf photographers Chris Burkard Photography, Ryan Struck, Kassia Meador, Matt Clark and Nolan Hall; fine artists Brainstorm Print + Design, Billy Name, the archival photographer of Andy Warhol‚Äôs Factory,Scott Szegeski, Virginia Lunt, and illustrator Matt Caputo; Chronicle Books; Archive New York, Guns Germs $teal, Rosa Swim, Toms Shoes; Williams Sonoma, Riverhorse Brewing Company, Industry City Distillery, and the Manhattan Sailing School.

Attendees got to see a sneak peek of a mini-documentary video of the Valpo Surf Project, produced by Billy Manchuck and Pancho Torres, and the premiere of the VSP‚Äôs Ambassdors Program, featuring professional surfers Kurt Rist and Christian ‚ÄúPunto‚Äù Gonzalez.

The Valpo Surf Project would especially like to thank all of the volunteers who helped to make this our most successful event to date; without your support this event wouldn‚Äôt have been possible. Thanks to our volunteer committee, including Lindsay Steuber, Pat Flaherty, Margaret Ryan, and Jenna Barzelay, who contributed time and energy to plan and execute this event. We‚Äôd also like to thank everyone who worked as volunteers to make this event a huge success including Jeff and Ann Marie Steuber, Michael Knapp, Briana Feola and Jason Snyder of Brainstorm, Caitlyn Warakomski, Britney Warakomski, Sam Rigby, Kathryn Armstrong, Ryan Holbrook, and Matt Caputo for t-shirt printing.  

And a huge thank you to Andrew Karp at the Centre for Social Innovation NYC for hosting the event at their incredible space, and Ketel One, Kona Brewing Company, and Runa for their incredible support.

The whole VSP team would like to thank everyone involved in making last Saturday's NYC Silent Auction Fundraiser the most successful event to date.  Our most heartfelt thanks goes out to the volunteers, donors, sponsors and attendees; without you, none of this would be possible.  We'll have more photos up later this week and look forward to the online premiere of the video screened in mid November!

Todo el equipo VSP quiere agradecer todos involucrados para hacer el evento en NYC del s√°bado pasado, nuestro evento mas exitoso hasta ahora.  Nuestras gracias sinceras va a todos los voluntarios, donadores, auspiciadores, y asistentes; sin ustedes, esto no habr√≠a sido posible.  Publicamos mas fotos en la semana y todos deben estar atentos al estreno online del video que mostramos durante el evento en noviembre!

column7:
As the winter months fade into spring, VSP surf sessions are starting back up on a consistent basis and our students are fully motivated.  The water's warming up, the sun's starting to shine and participants are donning neoprene to get back into the surf. Check out some more photos at http://bit.ly/17dNkJd for the latest sessions.

______________

Mientras que los meses del invierno cambian a primavera, las sesiones de surf de VSP est√°n empezando con consistencia y nuestros estudiantes est√°n motivados.  El agua empieza a entibiar, el sol est√° saliendo y los participantes est√°n listos en sus trajes para meterse al surf.  Revisan algunas de las fotos de las √∫ltimas sesiones http://bit.ly/17dNkJd.

column7:
CPR Classes with Naval Rescue Swimmer | Clases de RCP con Nadador de Rescate

Last year, Chilean Naval rescue swimmer Joel Acevedo gave a comprehensive CPR tutorial to a group of older VSP participants in conjunction with English classes.  Acevedo incorporated his experience with open ocean swimming and rescue operations to deliver an informative lesson about assessing situational risk and the proper CPR technique.

A big thanks to Joel Acevedo for leading this class and teaching VSP students valuable skills that will help improve their confidence in the surf and dealing with emergency situations. 

El a√±o pasado, nadador de rescate de la armada chilena, Joel Acevedo, dio una clase comprensiva de RCP a un grupo de nuestros alumnos mayores durante una sesi√≥n de ingl√©s. √âl incorpor√≥ su experiencia con nataci√≥n en mar abierto y m√©todos de rescate para entregar a nuestros estudiantes una lecci√≥n bien informativa sobre evaluaci√≥n de riesgos y t√©cnica correcta de RCP

Miles de grac√≠as para Joel por ense√±ar a los participantes del VSP habilidades valiosas que les ayudar√°n a subir su confianza en las olas y las situaciones de emergencia.

Mientras que el semestre termina, el VSP le gustar√≠a agradecer a nuestro equipo de voluntarios, la mayor√≠a de los cuales est√°n estudiando como estudiantes de intercambio en Valpara√≠so, por el tiempo y la pasi√≥n que han dedicado a la organizaci√≥n en los √∫ltimos meses. El √©xito de la organizaci√≥n s√≥lo es posible con su ayuda y apoyo incansable. Gracias a todos! Los vamos a echar de menos!

As the university semester ends in Chile, the VSP would like to thank our volunteer team, most of whom are studying as exchange students in Valpara√≠so, for the time and passion that they've dedicated to the organization over the last months. The success of the organization is only possible with your tireless help and support. Thank you all! We're going to miss you!

column7: Al principio de mayo, Valpo Surf Project se vincul√≥ con varias organizaciones medioambientales sin fines de lucro para trabajar con mas de 115 voluntarios en una limpieza de playa en Caleta Portales, una de las playas principales de Valpara√≠so.    Por estar asociado con el Greenpeace - Equipo de Voluntarios Valpara√≠so, Sea Shepherd Chile, Valpo Interviene, and Rotaract Club of Valpara√≠so, un equipo de participantes y voluntarios recogieron 400 kilos de basura y materiales reciclables de la playa.  Aseguran a revisar el link al video de la limpieza abajo y las fotos del evento.  In early May, the Valpo Surf Project teamed up with a number of local environmental non-profits and engaged more than 115 volunteers in a beach clean at Playa Caleta Portales, one of Valpara√≠so‚Äôs principal beaches.       By partnering up with the Valpara√≠so Chapter of Greenpeace, Sea Shepherd Chile, Valpo Interviene, and Rotaract Club of Valpara√≠so, a team of VSP participants and volunteers collected more than 400 kilograms of trash and recyclable materials from the beach.  Make sure to check out the link to the video below and the photos of the event.   http://vimeo.com/66357759

column7:
El 5 de Junio, cinco voluntarios de VSP viajaron hacia el sur a Pichilemu para ver el Quiksilver Ceremonial de 2013 presentado por Subaru. Desafortunadamente, el campeonato fue cancelado porque las olas nunca alcanzaron los 7 metros predecidos. A pesar de todo, los espectadores disfrutaron 2 horas de una ‚ÄúSesi√≥n de Expresi√≥n‚Äù de 24 de los mejores surfistas del mundo.

----------------------------------

On June 5th, five VSP volunteers packed up and headed south to catch The 2013 Quiksilver Ceremonial Chile presented by Subaru. The wave competition was unfortunately canceled due to an originally projected 15 foot-swell not reaching the necessary heights. Despite the cancelation, spectators were treated to a two hour ‚ÄúExpression Session‚Äù by 24 of the worlds best surfers.

column7:
Learn about the VSP‚Äôs new skate program and how you can help by donating skateboards, skateboard accessories, and safety gear, PARTICULARLY HELMETS!  If you are located in the New York City, Miami, or Los Angeles area---or are willing to ship to those areas--- please contact jsteuber@valposurfproject.com if you have gear you would like to donate!    

Aprende mas del programa de skate de VSP y como puedes ayudar por donar patinetas y accessorios de patinaje, incluyendo equipo de seguridad, PARTICULARMENTE CASCOS!  Si est√°s en Santiago o Valpara√≠so/Vi√±a del Mar y tienes algo para donar por favor contacta con jsteuber@valposurfproject.com.    
________________________________    

Throughout the summer months the Valpo Surf Project opened up a new series of skateboarding and rollerblading classes available to our students.  Skate classes have been a great way to motivate students to stay active and fit for surfing when we didn‚Äôt have the resources to get to the beach.    

While the skate club has had humble beginnings with a few pair of donated rollerblades and borrowed skateboards, we want to expand the resources to offer skate classes to more students.  Our first priority in moving forward with skateboard classes is to ensure the safety of our students.  We are very much in need of safety equipment so please contact jsteuber@valposurfproject.com to coordinate an in kind donation.    _________________________________   

Durante los meses del verano, Valpo Surf Project empez√≥ un nuevo taller de patinaje (con patines y patinetas) disponibles para nuestros estudiantes.  Las clases de patinaje han sido una buena manera para motivar los estudiantes a ser activos y en forma para el surf cuando no hemos tenido los recursos a llegar a la playa.  

Mientras que el taller de patinaje ha tenido origen humilde con algunos patines donados y patinetas prestadas, queremos expandir los recursos para ofrecer clases de patinaje para mas estudiantes.  Nuestra prioridad principal en seguir adelante con los talleres es asegurar la seguridad de los estudiantes.  Nosotros necesitamos equipo de seguridad as√≠ que por favor contacta con jsteuber@valposurfproject.com para coordinar su donaci√≥n.

Al final de enero el equipo Valpo Surf Project fue a las playas Baron y Placeres para limpiar dos de las playas principales de la ciudad que estaban llenas de basura tirada durante las celebraciones del A√±o Nuevo en Valpara√≠so.  Organizado por el Sea Shepherd Conservation Society Chile, el Valpo Surf Project junt√≥ mas que 25 voluntarios y estudiantes para juntarse con mas que 100 voluntarios de otras organizaciones en esta gran limpieza.  Otras organizaciones participantes incluyen los cuerpos de voluntarios de Sea Shepherd de la V Regi√≥n y Regi√≥n Metropolitana, Servicio Nacional de Menores (SENAME), Cuerpo de Botes Salvavidas de Valpara√≠so, la Municipalidad de Valpara√≠so y el Puerto Deportivo de Valpara√≠so.  

Gracias a todos los voluntarios y estudiantes que vinieron para apoyar esta actividad para proteger los oc√©anos de la regi√≥n costera de Valpara√≠so.        ____________________________________  

At the end of January the Valpo Surf Project team headed to Valpara√≠so‚Äôs Playa Baron and Playa Placeres to clean two of the city‚Äôs principal beaches that had been scattered with trash after Valpara√≠so‚Äôs New Year‚Äôs celebrations.  Organized by Sea Shepherd Conservation Society Chile, the Valpo Surf Project brought together 25 volunteers and students to join more than 100 volunteers from other organizations in this large scale beach clean.  Other participating organizations included members of Sea Shepherd from Chile‚Äôs 5th Region and Metropolitan Region, Servicio Nacional de Menores (SENAME), Cuerpo de Botes Salvavidas de Valpara√≠so, the Municipality of Valpara√≠so, and the Puerto Deportivo of Valpara√≠so.    

Thanks to all of the volunteers and students who came out to support this latest effort to protect the water quality of Valpara√≠so‚Äôs coastal region.

New Year's is always a great time in Valparaiso. Hopefully next year the adults can step up and be responsible the mess left in the wake of the party. Fortunately, the VSP kids were there to do some major clean up at the city's beaches after the festivities concluded.

El A√±o Nuevo siempre es una noche increible en Valparaiso. Ojala que el proximo a√±o los adultos puedan ser responsable por su basura despues de la fiesta. Gracias a los alumnos del VSP que tomaron la responsibilidad de limpiar algunas de las playas de Valparaiso.

Today is the last day to make tax deductible donations for 2012! We are just $1,800 shy of reaching our fundraising goal of $10,000 this holiday season. The VSP was created by small donations from all of you, and we need your support for continued success. Please take a moment and give whatever you can to help us reach our goal. Every gift has a major impact on our students' lives.

Thank you so much and we wish you all a very happy new year!

http://www.valposurfproject.com/donate-now/

column7:
Jueves el 20 de Diciembre el VSP  llev√≥ a cabo el primer evento para recaudar fondos  en Chile en Zen Club Boutique, el innovador restaurante de sushi y discoteque en Santiago.  Todos los fondos recaudados del evento van a beneficiar la Vanpaign, nuestra campa√±a de recaudar fondos para una nueva van para la organizaci√≥n.  Fue un gran √©xito con mucha gente y una noche de diversi√≥n incluyendo tragos, sushi y rifas de Voraz Pizza Vitacura, Juan Pablo Barrientos, Surfer‚Äôs Paradise, y Deportes Tenderini. 

Gracias a todos los que vinieron a apoyar el VSP, todos los voluntarios que ayudaron a hacer el evento exitoso, A Lo Gringo por proveer la m√∫sica, y todos los auspiciadores del evento incluyendo Zen Club Boutique, Voraz Pizza Vitacura, Juan Pablo Barrientos, Surfer‚Äôs Paradise, y Deportes Tenderini.  Y muchas gracias a Fernanda Vallade por organizar el evento!   
 ______________________________    

On Thursday December 20th, the VSP hosted its first fundraising event in Chile at Zen Club Boutique, Santiago‚Äôs premiere night club and sushi bar.  All proceeds raised from the event will benefit the Vanpaign, our campaign to purchase a new van for the organization.  The event was a great success with a packed house, and fun night with drinks, sushi and raffle prizes from Voraz Pizza Vitacura, Juan Pablo Barrientos, Surfer‚Äôs Paradise, and Deportes Tenderini.    

Thanks to everyone who came out to support the VSP, everyone who volunteered and helped to make the event a success, A Lo Gringo for providing a great soundtrack, and all of the sponsors of the event including Zen Club Boutique, Voraz Pizza Vitacura, Juan Pablo Barrientos, Surfer‚Äôs Paradise, and Deportes Tenderini.  And a huge thank you to Fernanda Vallade for organizing the event!

After a successful first 10K race in September, the VSP running team took up the challenge again this past Sunday, October 21st, at the Third Annual Family Run held by the Firefighters Association of Vi√±a del Mar.  

Congratulations to VSP participant Nik Corvalan (age 17) for finishing in the top 20 and congratulations to Catalina Pulgar Nu√±ez and Ayleen Flores for reducing their 10K time by 17 minutes in just 20 days ‚Äì an incredibly impressive feat!   

Special thanks to cofounder Andres Ponce and volunteer Michelle Fern√°ndez for running with VSP participants and supporting VSP in this grueling race.  The VSP team looks forward to many more successful runs in the future!       

Despu√©s de una corrida exitosa de 10K en septiembre, el equipo VSP corri√≥ nuevamente este domingo 21 de octubre, la 3da Corrida Familiar del Cuerpo de Bomberos de Vi√±a del Mar.  

Felicitaciones a alumno de VSP Nik Corvalan (17) quien lleg√≥ a los veinte primeros y felicitaciones a alumnas Catalina Pulgar Nu√±ez (13) and Ayleen Flores (17) por bajando su tiempo de 10K por 17 minutos ‚Äì un logro incre√≠ble!   

Muchas gracias a co-fundador Andr√©s Ponce y voluntaria Michelle Fern√°ndez por correr con el equipo VSP y apoyarnos en esta ardua tarea.  El equipo VSP espera tener muchas m√°s corridas exitosas en el futuro!

This past Sunday, September 30, the VSP family took a break from surfing to show off their athletic prowess at the 2nd Annual TPS Marathon.  Congratulations to VSP participants Catalina Pulgar Nu√±ez (age 13), Ayleen Flores (age 17), and Nik Corvalan (age 17) for their amazing effort in training for and finishing the grueling 10K race.  Thanks to their hard work, Catalina placed 96th in her age group, Ayleen placed 31st, and Nik placed 13th out of over 3,000 race participants.  Together with volunteers Brendan Buckland, Luna Toledo, and Michelle Fern√°ndez, these VSP stars ran through Valpo‚Äôs scenic port area while proudly sporting their VSP caps and face paint.

Special thanks to the fans who came to support the VSP team: VSP Cofounder and Director Henry Myer, VSP participant B√°rbara del Canto, volunteers Camila Valenzuela and Claudio Vilches, and proud VSP parents Mrs. Yanina Corvalan and Mr. Flores.  Eager to run again, the VSP family will also be running in the 3rd Annual Firefighter Association of Vi√±a del Mar 10K race on October 21st.  We hope to see you there!



Este domingo pasado, la familia VSP suspendi√≥ sus sesiones semanales de surf para mostrar su proeza atl√©tica en la segunda media marat√≥n de Valpara√≠so.  Felicitaciones a los alumnos de VSP que participaron - Catalina Pulgar Nu√±ez (13), Ayleen Flores (17), y Nik Corvalan (17) ‚Äì por sus esfuerzos y dedicaci√≥n incre√≠ble a entrenar y terminar esta carrera dur√≠sima de 10 kil√≥metros.  Gracias a sus esfuerzos, Catalina gan√≥ el 96 lugar de su categor√≠a de edad, Ayleen gan√≥ el 31 lugar, y Nik gan√≥ el 13 lugar entre m√°s de 3 mil participantes en la corrida.  Junto con voluntarios Brendan Buckland, Luna Toledo, y Michelle Fern√°ndez, estas estrellas de VSP corrieron orgullosamente por el puerto pintoresco de Valpo con sus gorros y caras pintadas con las letras de VSP.

Muchas gracias a los fans que vinieron a apoyar al equipo de VSP: co-fundador y director de VSP Henry Myer, alumna de VSP B√°rbara del Canto, voluntarios Camila Valenzuela y Claudio Vilches, y padres orgullosos de VSP Sra. Yanina Corvalan y Sr. Flores.  Emocionados por correr de nuevo, la familia VSP correr√° en la Corrida Familiar de los Bomberos de Vi√±a del Mar el 21 de Octubre.  Esperamos verlos all√≠!

column7:
This past Saturday September 15, the Valpo Surf Project hosted its 4th Annual Silent Auction Fundraiser in New York City, with more than 65 people in attendance.  Held on the rooftop terrace of the Associated Press offices, the event brought together long time supporters in the NYC area and engaged new donors who came to learn more about the VSP mission.    

The evening was a great opportunity to celebrate and sustain the work of the Valpo Surf Project and the event‚Äôs success was possible only through the active support of so many people.  We would like to thank everyone who came out to attend the event, Pat Flaherty and everyone at the Associated Press for allowing us to use their space,  Kona Brewing Company and Ketel One Vodka for the beverages, Ann Marie Steuber for catering excellent food, Brainstorm Print and Design for crafting the event poster, and Lindsay Steuber for coordinating much of the silent auction donations, and all the volunteers who helped set up and break down the event.    

We‚Äôd also like to thank all of the contributors to our silent auction  Malwitz Custom Surfboards, Thomas Campbell, Chris Burkard, Ryan Struck, Kassia Meador, Joe Hodnicki of Sharing the Stoke, Chronicle Books, Brainstorm Print and Design, Matt Caputo, Eclectic Current Custom Kicks, Soul Polish Yoga, and Ann Marie Steuber.  
_________________  
Este S√°bado pasado, el 15 de septiembre, Valpo Surf Project acogi√≥ su Cuarto Evento Anual de Recaudar fondos en New York City, con mas que 65 personas en asistencia.  Se llev√≥ a cabo en la terraza de aire libre de las oficinas del Associated Press, el evento reuni√≥ a partidarios viejos y nuevos del Valpo Surf Project para ofrecer su apoyo y aprender m√°s de las iniciativas nuevas del programa.  

La noche fue una grande oportunidad para celebrar y sostener el trabajo del Valpo Surf Project y el √©xito del evento solo fue posible por el apoyo activo de mucha gente.  Nos gustar√≠a dar gracias a la gente que asisti√≥ el evento, Pat Flaherty y todos del Associated Press por permitirnos a usar el espacio,  Kona Brewing Company y Ketel One Vodka por donar los tragos, Ann Marie Steuber por preparar la comida, Brainstorm Print and Design por dise√±ar el afiche del evento, Lindsay Steuber por coordinar muchas donaciones del remate, y toda la gente que nos ayud√≥ a preparar antes de y limpiar despues del evento.  

Tambi√©n, nos gustar√≠a dar las gracias tambi√©n a toda la gente que contribuyeron al remate: Malwitz Custom Surfboards, Thomas Campbell, Chris Burkard, Ryan Struck, Kassia Meador, Joe Hodnicki of Sharing the Stoke, Chronicle Books, Brainstorm Print and Design, Matt Caputo, Eclectic Current Custom Kicks, Soul Polish Yoga, y Ann Marie Steuber.

column7:
Today we say good-bye to our dear friend Kathryn Armstrong, the founder/director of Foto Valpo. All of us here at the VSP are extremely proud of her and we will miss her love, leadership, and energy.

Kathryn began formulating the curriculum for Foto Valpo in 2010. After spending the summer and fall of 2011 fundraising with assistant Danielle Frye and VSP Development Director Wiley Todd she launched the Foto Valpo pilot program in March of 2012. Foto Valpo's first semester saw 16 VSP students participate and culminated in a wonderful exhibition of the students work on May 25, 2012.

Although Kathryn is returning home to Thomaston, Maine, USA she has left her mark on the Valpo Surf Project and Foto Valpo will continue on. We wish you the best Kathryn and hope you come back for a  visit soon!

A huge thanks to partnering organization A Warm Current for donating 6 wetsuits and 5 pairs of booties to the VSP and thanks to Dar Vanderbeck for bringing them all down to Chile for us.  As winter approaches, staying warm is priority number one for our students.  If you‚Äôre located in the Northern California or the Pacific Northwest and have used wetsuits to donated, check out their donation drop off centers http://www.warmcurrent.org/work/locations/ or contact them directly info@warmcurrent.org.   

Muchas gracias a la organizaci√≥n asociada A Warm Current por donar 6 trajes y 5 conjuntos de botines al VSP y gracias a Dar Vanderbeck por transportarlos a Chile.  Mientras el invierno se acerca, la prioridad mas importante para nuestros estudiantes en el agua es mantener el calor durante sesiones de surf.  Si est√°s ubicado en California del Norte o el Noroeste del Pac√≠fico de los Estados Unidos y quiere donar trajes, revisa sus centros para donaciones http://www.warmcurrent.org/work/locations/ o les contacta directamente por info@warmcurrent.org.

Este S√°bado pasado, un grupo de voluntarios y 10 estudiantes recibieron su primera lecci√≥n en laminaci√≥n de tablas de surf en el taller de shaper local de Re√±aca Hueso Carranza.  La tabla, shapeado en Octubre con fabricante de tablas Mauricio Donoso de Schiestl Chile Surf Boards, recibi√≥ el tratamiento total de preparaci√≥n, laminaci√≥n, y glass durante el taller.

Porque no hay mucho espacio en los talleres de laminaci√≥n y solo tuvimos una cantidad limitada de mascaras, los estudiantes de VSP se turnaron trabajando en el taller y la mayor√≠a se involucraron directamente por aplicar resina.  Despu√©s de horas en el taller, un asado para almuerzo, y un d√≠a de luchar con un cielo nublado, esperando la resina UV a secar, por fin los chicos tuvieron la oportunidad de tomar la tabla en las manos por la primera vez desde lo hicimos en Pichilemu.

Gracias a todos que apoyaron este proyecto de hacer una tabla en colaboraci√≥n.  Gracias a Hueso Carranza por laminar y terminar la tabla, Mauricio Donoso de Schiestl Chile Surf Boards por shapear, George Ordenes de Surfer‚Äôs Paradise por donar el foam, Cristian Punto Gonzalez por todos los contactos de facilitar el proyecto, Shaggy y Luna por manejar y sacar fotos, y Ella Farnsworth por grabar.   
  
____________________________________________________________

This past Saturday, a group of VSP volunteers and 10 students got their first lesson in surfboard glassing and finishing at the workshop of local Re√±aca shaper Hueso Carranza.  The board, shaped in October with Pichilemu-based Mauricio Donoso from Schiestl Chile Surf Boards, received the full treatment of preparation, glass and hot coat during the workshop.

Space was tight in the glassing room and we had a limited amount of respirators on hand, so students took turns in the workshop and most had the opportunity to get their hands directly involved in helping Hueso apply resin.  After hours in the glassing room, a lunch time barbecue, and a full day of battling an overcast sky for the UV resin to dry, the kids finally got the opportunity to hold the board under their arms for the first time since it was shaped.       

Thanks to everyone who made this collaborative board project possible.  Thanks to  Hueso Carranza for glassing, Mauricio Donoso at Schiestl Chile Surf Boards for shaping, George Ordenes at Surfer‚Äôs Paradise for donating the blank, Cristian Punto Gonzalez for putting us in touch with people to facilitate the project, Shaggy and Luna for driving and snapping photos all day, and Ella Farnsworth for filming.

column7:
In early March the VSP had the pleasure of hosting artists Briana Feola and Jason Snyder, owners and operators of Brainstorm Print and Design, to conduct a series of screenprinting workshops for VSP students.  The Brainstorm duo, who created the logo for the organization, have supported the VSP since its beginning through creating our visual identity, contributing print donations to silent auctions, and designing event posters.    

After years of contributing to the program, Jay and Briana finally got the chance to come and meet the kids they‚Äôve been so influential in supporting and get their hands dirty pulling screens with our students.  They came prepared with squeegees, screens, and designs to teach the process of screenprinting and we took a break from regularly scheduled English classes to make some art.  At the end of each session, all of the kids had some new art-related English vocabulary, introduction to a new skill, and fresh prints to put on the walls.   

Thanks so much to Jason and Briana of Brainstorm for coming down and giving both the kids and the directors and volunteers an experience they‚Äôll never forget.  We hope you can make it back soon.   
_______________________________  

Al principio de marzo, VSP tuvo el placer de recibir los artistas Briana Feola y Jason Snyder, due√±os de Brainstorm Print and Design, para hacer unos talleres de serigraf√≠a para los estudiantes del programa.  Los dos de Brainstorm, quienes dise√±aron el logo de Valpo Surf Project, han apoyado a la organizaci√≥n desde sus comienzos por hacer nuestra identidad visual, dise√±ar los afiches de eventos para recaudar fondos, y donar obras de arte por remate en los eventos.  

Despu√©s de a√±os de contribuir al programa, Jason and Briana finalmente recibieron la oportunidad de venir y conocer a los j√≥venes que han apoyado en el pasado mientras ensuciando las manos con serigraf√≠a.  Ellos vinieron preparados con todo el equipo para ense√±ar el proceso de serigraf√≠a y tomamos un recreo de las clases regulares de ingl√©s para hacer arte.  Al final de cada sesi√≥n, todos los chicos aprendieron vocabulario nuevo de ingl√©s relacionado al arte, la introducci√≥n a un conocimiento nuevo, y obras de arte para poner en sus paredes.  

Muchas gracias a Jason y Briana de Brainstorm para venir y dar una experiencia inolvidable a los estudiantes, voluntarios, y directores del Valpo Surf Project.  Esperamos que vayan a regresar pronto.

column7:
On Saturday February 25, the Valpo Surf Project co-organized and executed a beach clean with local environmental group Valpo Interviene at Playa Portales in Valpara√≠so.  More than 40 people came to lend a hand in cleaning up the beach, including 23 students and volunteers from the VSP, as well as members of Valpo Interviene, and environmental organizations Geociclos Ecolog√≠a Urbana and the Paula Quintana campaign for mayor.  

Beach clean participants worked together to collect over 30 bags of trash from Valpara√≠so‚Äôs Playa Portales, the city‚Äôs most popular beach.  Additionally, the beach cleaners separated out glass and plastic bottles from the rest of the trash for proper disposal and recycling.

Thanks to all the participants for their help including members of the Valpo Surf Project, Valpo Interviene, Geociclos Ecolog√≠a Urbana, and the Paula Quintana mayoral campaign.  Let‚Äôs organize another event soon.

_______________________________________________ 

El s√°bado 25 de febrero, Valpo Surf Project co-organiz√≥ y llev√≥ a cabo una limpieza de playa con grupo medioambiental llamado Valpo Interviene en Playa Portales, ubicado en Valpara√≠so.  Mas de 40 personas asistieron para echar una mando en limpiar la playa, incluyendo 23 alumnos y voluntarios del VSP, y tambi√©n miembros de Valpo Interviene y organizaciones medioambientales Geociclos Ecolog√≠a Urbana y la campa√±a de la alcadesa de Paula Quintana.

Participantes de la limpieza de la playa trabajaron juntos para coleccionar mas de 30 bolsas de basura en Playa Portales, la playa principal de la ciudad de Valpara√≠so.  Adicionalmente, los voluntarios separaron las botellas de plastico y vidrio de la basura para reciclarlas.  

Gracias a todos los participantes por su ayuda, incluso miembros del Valpo Surf Project, Valpo Interviene, Geociclos Ecolog√≠a Urbana, y la campa√±a de la alcaldesa Paula Quintana.  Organizamos otra limpieza pronto.

column7:
VSP Fighting Cigarette Butts on Beaches with Rip Curl Planet and Proplaya

VSP has linked up with environmental organizations Rip Curl Planet and Proplaya to fight against cigarette butts being dumped on beaches, one of the principle forms of trash that litters beaches across the world.  The two organizations have teamed up to produce a case that fits over the bottom of cigarette packs, where beach goers can properly dispose of cigarette butts instead of discarding them on beaches.

After a surf session in Con Con, some members of the VSP team went to the fifth sector of Re√±aca to distribute cases to people vacationing on the beach and talk about the harmful effects of cigarette butts on the beach.

Check out some of the facts about cigarette butts on beach contamination, written on the cases to remind the public of the importance of proper cigarette butt disposal:

Cigarette butts account for 37% of all trash on beaches.
Each cigarette butt can contaminate 50 liters of water
Cigarette butts take 5 years to biodegrade.
Of the cigarette butts littering beaches, 30% of them will eventually end in the ocean. 

Source: http://www.chilesurf.cl/?p=15326

____________________________________

VSP Lucha Contra las Colillas de Cigarros en la Playa con Rip Curl Planet y Proplaya

El VSP ha vinculado con organizaciones medioambientales Rip Curl Planet y Proplaya para contra las colillas de cigarros botadas en la playa, uno de los tipos de desecho mas encontrados en las playas de todo el mundo.  Las dos organizaciones se han juntado para hacer y distribuir una funda para cajetillas de cigarros, donde las personas que visitan la playa pueden descartar sus colillas en vez de botarlas en la playa.

Despu√©s de una sesi√≥n de surf en Con Con, un grupo de chicos del Valpo Surf Project fueron al quinto sector de Re√±aca para distribuir las fundas y hablar con la gente all√° acerca de los efectos negativos de colillas botadas en la playa.

Revisa mas informaci√≥n acerca del v√≠nculo entre colillas y contaminaci√≥n de playas:

Las colillas de cigarro, estas son un 37% del total de la basura en las playas.
Cada colilla llega a contaminar 50 litros de agua.  
 Demoran en biodegradarse cerca de 5 a√±os.
 Aproximadamente el 30% de esas colillas se va al mar.     

Fuente de informaci√≥n: http://www.chilesurf.cl/?p=15326

column7:
Each year the turn of the new year means the official beginning of summer in Valpara√≠so and last Friday the older group of VSP students, along with directors and volunteers, got together to clean and repair boards to start off the season right.  The team got together to scrape wax, clean boards, and repair dings to get them ready for the water.  

Students and volunteers got a full lesson on basic board repair with fiberglass and polyester resin.  Each student learned how to identify dings, sand them to prepare for repair, and finally how to safely use polyester resin and fiberglass to seal the cracks.  We ended the day with an asado of chorizo, salsa, and grilled squash for the students.  And, director Henry Myer showed off his traditional Chilean dance skills and danced the cueca.

_________________________________________

Cada a√±o nuevo ac√° en Valpara√≠so significa el comienzo oficial del verano y el viernes pasado el grupo mayor de estudiantes VSP, con los directores y voluntarios, se juntaron para limpiar y reparar tablas para empezar la temporada correctamente.  El equipo se junt√≥ para raspar cera, limpiar las tablas, y reparar los hoyos para preparar las tablas para el agua.

Los estudiantes y voluntarios recibieron una lecci√≥n completa de reparaci√≥n b√°sica de tablas con fibra de vidrio y resina de poli√©ster.  Cada estudiante aprendi√≥ como identificar da√±os de una tabla, lijarlos para prepararlos para reparaci√≥n, y finalmente como usar resina de poli√©ster para cerrar los hoyos.   Terminamos el d√≠a con un asado de choripanes con pebre y zapallo italiano asado para los estudiantes.  Y, por supuesto, director Henry Myer mostr√≥ sus conocimientos de la danza tradicional de Chile y bail√≥ la cueca.

The Deadline For Submissions Has Been Extended!
To November 25th, so, hurry, send in your photography!

If you are a college or high school student living in Maine and enjoy photography, you may want to submit your work to our juried panel of photographers and critics for a chance to have your work exhibited during Portland's Art Walk on December 2nd. Please visit our website to learn more about how you can support student photographers in Valpo by donating your own work.

column7:
On October 22, the Valpo Surf Project hosted it‚Äôs 3rd Annual Silent Auction Fundraiser at the Crop to Cup Brew Bar in Gowanus, Brooklyn.  The event was a great success with over 60 people in attendance from across the tri-state area who enjoyed food, drink, and a full display of diverse items up for silent auction.

We‚Äôd like to thank everyone who showed their support by coming to the event, Alexis Grossman and Crop to Cup for opening up their event space, the Mainbrook Tavern and Steuber family for donating libations, and all of the artists and businesses who donated work to the silent auction including Chris Burkard, Dion Agius, Joe Hodnicki, Brainstorm Print and Design, Matt Caputo, Kathryn Armstrong, Bird in a Hole Birdhouses, Eclectic Current CustomKicks, Jacob Bluestone, Chronicle Books, Spitzer‚Äôs Corner, Early Bird Foods & Co., Nunu Chocolates, and Wines of Chile.

Also thank you to everyone who volunteered their time to work as event staff including Lindsay Steuber, Tom Meehan, Brit Warakomski, Marsha Larned, Catalina de la Barra and Dan and Connor from Crop to Cup for helping set up.  

_____________________________________

El 22 de Octubre, Valpo Surf Project  llev√≥ a cabo la tercera edici√≥n del Evento ‚ÄúRemate NYC‚Äù para recaudar fondos , esto se realiz√≥ en Crop to Cup Brew Bar in Gowanus, Brooklyn.  El evento fue un gran √©xito con mas de 60 personas que asistieron para disfrutar una noche de arte, diversi√≥n y cooperaci√≥n contando con una amplea variedad de articulos en el remate.

Queremos dar la gracias a toda la gente que asisti√≥ y apoy√≥ la organizaci√≥n, Alexis Grossman y Crop to Cup para ofrecer el espacio para el evento, Mainbrook Tavern y la familia Steuber para donar las bebidas, y todos los artistas y negocios que donaron obras al remate, incluyendo Chris Burkard, Dion Agius, Joe Hodnicki, Brainstorm Print and Design, Matt Caputo, Kathryn Armstrong, Bird in a Hole Birdhouses, Eclectic Current CustomKicks, Jacob Bluestone, Chronicle Books, Spitzer‚Äôs Corner, Early Bird Foods & Co., Nunu Chocolates, y Wines of Chile.  

Gracias tambi√©n a todas las personas que donaron su tiempo para trabajar como voluntarios durante el evento incluyendo Lindsay Steuber, Tom Meehan, Brit Warakomski, Marsha Larned, Catalina de la Barra  y Dan y Connor de Crop to Cup.

column7:
Student Art Exhibition
CALL TO ARTISTS!

If you are a college or high school student living in Maine and enjoy photography, you may want to submit your work to our juried panel of photographers and critics for a chance to have your work exhibited during Portland's Art Walk on December 2nd.  Please visit our website to learn more about how you can support student photographers in Valpo by donating your own work.

column7:
Winter has started in Chile and as a result, we‚Äôve put surf sessions on pause for the upcoming months.  However, in the last weeks of May, the Valpo Surf Project team took advantage of a few surf days regardless of the cold water temps of the coming winter.  Despite the change of seasons and conditions, VSP participants were excited to get in the water.  

Although the surf season has ended until spring, we‚Äôre going to continue with training sessions and physical activities like soccer and basketball games so the VSP students will stay in shape during the winter.  Stay tuned for more information and photos of our winter activities. 

En Chile el invierno ya ha empezado, y por eso vamos a poner las clases de surf en pausa.  Pero, en las √∫ltimas semanas de Mayo, el equipo Valpo Surf Project aprovech√≥ de algunos d√≠as de surf a pesar del agua fr√≠o del principio del invierno.  No obstante el cambio de clima los participantes estaban emocianados como siempre para disfrutar el agua.  

Aunque la temporada de surf se acab√≥ hasta la primavera, vamos a seguir con sesiones de entrenimiento y actividades f√≠sicas para que los chicos mantengan su forma durante el invierno.  Sigan atentos para mas informaci√≥n y fotos de las actividades del invierno.

column7:
The area of Valpara√≠so and Vi√±a del Mar is home to a number of universities that attract students from around Chile and international exchange students from abroad. Within the past month, the Valpo Surf Project has hosted a number of instructional surf outings for university students as a way to fundraise money to offset costs of participant surf trips, generate support in the community, and recruit volunteers for English classes. Here are some photos of the sessions that we‚Äôve enjoyed with some of our university supporters from Chile, the United States, Brazil, Argentina, and Germany. 

El √°rea de Valpara√≠so y Vi√±a del Mar es el hogar de varias universidades que atrayen estudiantes de todas partes de Chile y estudiantes internacionales. Durante el mes pasado, Valpo Surf Project ha hecho algunas excursiones instrucionales para universitarios como manera de recaudar fondos para las sesiones de surf de los participantes, generar apoyo en la comunidad, y enganchar voluntarios para las clases de ingl√©s. Ac√° hay algunas fotos de las sesiones que hemos disfrutado con nuestros apoyadores universitarios de Chile, los Estados Unidos, Brasil, Argentina, y Alemania.

column7: Between seeing Ramon Navarro get huge tubes during the big swell in Fiji last week and seeing June 15--the last day of the waiting period for Chile‚Äôs famous big wave contest--getting closer, we wanted to show a couple of photos from the Quiksilver Ceremonial in 2011.  Hopefully the waves will come to be able to run the event.  Enjoy the photos.   Entre ver Ramon Navarro tomar algunas de las olas mas grandes y tubadas de la √∫ltima marejada en Fiji y ver el 15 de junio--el √∫ltimo d√≠a en el periodo de espera para el famoso campeonato de olas grandes en Chile--acercando, quer√≠amos mostrar algunas fotos del Quiksilver Ceremonial del 2011.  Ojal√° que vengan olas para realizar el campeonato este a√±o.  Disfruten las fotos.

column7:
El 23 de Febrero el equipo de VSP recibi√≥ un visita del Gobernador de Valpara√≠so, Sr. Pablo Zu√±iga Jiliberto, y el Coordinador del Sistema de Protecci√≥n Social, Sr. Mauricio Perez Espinoza, y La Coordinadora del Programa Jefas de Hogar, Ingrid Le√≥n Rivera, para entregar paquetes de √∫tiles escolares a los participantes de Valpo Surf Project. Despu√©s de una presentaci√≥n de los directores de VSP, el Gobernador Zu√±iga dio un discurso de apoyo al proyecto, aplaudiendo un modelo alternativo de educaci√≥n que es entretenido, personalizado, y afecta la comunidad directamente.

Muchas gracias al Gobernador Pablo Zu√±iga Jiliberto, todos los representantes de su oficina que ayudaron a realizar este evento, todos los participantes de VSP y sus familias por asistir la reuni√≥n, y los vecinos de Cerro Mariposa que ayudaron a organizar el evento, particularmente Patrica Morales, Sandra Paolo Mena O√±ate, y Pedro Lopez Aros.

On February 23 the VSP team received a visit from the Governor of Valpara√≠so, Pablo Zu√±iga Jiliberto, and the Coordinator of the Social Protection System, Mauricio Perez Espinoza, and Coordinator of the Female Heads of Household Program, Ingrid Le√≥n Rivera, to distribute school supplies packets to Valpo Surf Project participants. After a presentation of the program by the Valpo Surf Project directors, Governor Zu√±iga gave a speech to support the project, applauding an alternative model of education that is entertaining, individualized and directly affects the community.

We would like to thank Governor Pablo Zu√±iga Jiliberto, the representatives of his office who helped to realize this event, all the participants of VSP and their families for attending the meeting, and the community members who helped to organize the meeting, particularly Patricia Morales, Sandra Paolo Mena O√±ate, y Pedro Lopez Aros.

column7:
El 5 de Febrero VSP particip√≥ en una limpieza de la playa en La Boca, Con Con como una parte del D√≠a Nacional Limpiando Tu Playa. Organizado por la organizaci√≥n Limpiando Playas, la limpieza en La Boca fue un gran √©xito y se llev√≥ a cabo al mismo tiempo que limpiezas por todo el pa√≠s de Chile, incluyendo Antofogasta, La Serena, Pichilemu, Iquique, y Quintero.

Los miembros del equipo VSP, quienes eran una parte grande de los participantes en el evento de Con Con, son orgullosos de estar involucrado en una demostraci√≥n de solidaridad con cientos de surfistas por todo de Chile.

El evento, auspiciado la compa√±√≠a que fabrica productos de limpieza Virutex y la marca Chilena de trajes Stoked, concluy√≥ con una charla ecol√≥gica por el organizador del evento Pedro Figueroa y surfista local Constanza Fernandez. Muchas gracias a todos que participaron y a todos los auspicios y organizadores.

___________________________________

On February 5, VSP participated in a beach clean at Playa La Boca in Con Con as part of National Clean Your Beach Day.  Organized by the Chilean nonprofit organization Limpiando Playas, the La Boca cleanup effort was an enormous success and took place at the same time as beach cleans throughout the country, including Antofogasta, La Serena, Pichilemu, Iquique, and Quintero.

The members of the VSP team, who made up a large portion of the participants in the Con Con event, are all proud to be involved in such a show of solidarity with hundreds of other surfers throughout Chile.

The event, which was sponsored by the manufacturer of cleaning products Virutex and Chilean wetsuit brand Stoked, concluded with an ecological roundtable discussion with participants, event organizer Pedro Figueroa and local surfer Constanza Fernandez.  Thank you to everyone who participated and to the event sponsors and organizers.

Todos se juntaron para una colaci√≥n de la Navidad completa con galletas y chocolate caliente y hicimos un intercambio de regalos de amigo secreto.  Y por supuesto, el Viejo Pascuero asisti√≥ a la celebraci√≥n para distribuir los regalos, sin embargo el Viejo fue un poco parecido a uno de los directores de Valpo Surf Project.

Here are some photos of a small holiday party the Valpo Surf Project conducted with program participants and some of their family members.  Everyone got together for snacks-complete with cookies and hot chocolate-and a Secret Santa present exchange.  Of course, Santa Claus was in attendance, although he did look a little bit like one of the Valpo Surf Project directors.

column7:
El 11 de Diciembre, el equipo entero de Valpo Surf Project de 45 personas, incluyendo participantes, directores, voluntarios, y varias madres de participantes actuando como monitores, hizo una excursi√≥n educativa a Playa Grande en Quintay. El prop√≥sito del viaje a Playa Grande, una playa 45 minutos al sur de Valpara√≠so en condici√≥n impecable, fue a introducir un contraste a las playas descuidadas del √°rea metropolitano de Valpara√≠so y expandir los conocimientos de la regi√≥n costera de los participantes.

Quisimos mostrar la potencial de las playas locales de los participantes por mostrarlos una comunidad de la costa que ha trabajado juntos para proveer la infraestructura y conciencia necesaria para mantener una playa limpia. Aunque quer√≠amos surfear all√° con los chicos, el mar fue demasiado grande para el aprendizaje; sin embargo, el gran tama√±o no par√≥ los participantes y voluntarios de ponerse los trajes y nadar en la espuma cerca a la playa.

Muchas gracias a la Municipalidad de Valpara√≠so por su apoyo de proveer transportaci√≥n por el viaje, todos los participantes para venir, todos los voluntarios y monitores familiares que contribuyeron a una actividad exitosa, y a Cano de Nativos Quintay Surf por trabajar como salvavidas.

__________________________

On December 11, the entire Valpo Surf Project team of 45 people, including participants, directors, volunteers, and a number of parent chaperones, made a day-long beach excursion to Playa Grande in Quintay. The purpose of the trip to Playa Grande, a beach 45 minutes south of Valpara√≠so in impeccable condition, was to introduce a contrast to the littered beaches of the Valpara√≠so metropolitan area and expand participants‚Äô knowledge of the coastline.

We wanted to show participants the potential of their local beaches by bringing them to a beach community that has worked together to provide the infrastructure and stewardship needed to maintain a healthy beach. Although we wanted to get in some surfing with the kids, the swell was a bit too big for learning; but, that didn‚Äôt stop the participants and volunteers from putting on their wetsuits to flop around in the shorebreak.

Thanks to the Municipality of Valpara√≠so for their generous support of providing transportation for the day, all the volunteers and parent chaperones who helped to make the day a success, and Cano from Nativos Quintay Surf for lifeguarding.

column7:
El 18 de Diciembre, los participantes de Valpo Surf Project ejecutaron la iniciativa ‚ÄúLimpiando Mi Barrio,‚Äù una limpieza de la comunidad del Cerro Mariposa, el hogar de la mayor√≠a de los participantes de VSP y donde se ubica la Junta de Vecinos 21 la Obra donde hacemos clases de ingl√©s.

Desde un comienzo, el componente medioambiental de VSP se ha tratado de educaci√≥n y acci√≥n de limpiezas de las playas que usamos para las clases de surf. Sin embargo, despu√©s de algunos eventos en playas cercanas, el participante Jesus Miranda Aguilera (15 a√±os), sugiri√≥ que llev√°semos los esfuerzos de cuidar el mediambiente m√°s cerca del hogar y empez√≥ a planificar un proyecto de recolecci√≥n de basura en su barrio con los otros participantes del programa.

Todos los aspectos de la actividad, desde juntar materiales necesarios, a organizar las √°reas y equipos de limpieza, a la publicidad en el barrio, fueron planificados por los participantes mayores de VSP. Fue un gran √©xito, que no s√≥lo demuestra un paso en que los participantes est√°n tomando conciencia respecto de su entorno, sino que tambi√©n, que son capaces de desarrollar acciones proactivamente para cambiar y mejorar el medioambiente y el entorno del barrio. Esta es la forma en que los ni√±os nos ense√±an que si cuentan con el espacio y la confianza necesaria es posible construir un proyecto solidario exitoso, orientado hacia la comunidad y el barrio y liderado por ellos mismos.

La iniciativa ha sido una gran satisfacci√≥n para VSP , la comunidad y para ellos mismos. Gracias a todos los participantes, ni√±os y ni√±as, voluntarios, familias, y vecinos que dedicaron su tiempo a esta iniciativa. Gracias tambi√©n a Diego Figueroa de la organizaci√≥n Limpiando Playas por proveer las bolsas y guantes para la actividad.

________________________________________

On December 18, Valpo Surf Project participants executed the ‚ÄúLimpiando Mi Barrio‚Äù initiative, a neighborhood clean in Cerro Mariposa, home to the majority of VSP‚Äôs participants and the community center where English classes are held.

In the past, VSP has concentrated its environmental efforts on education and action through clean-ups of local beaches used for surf sessions. However, after a number of events at nearby beaches, 15 year old VSP participant Jesus Miranda Aguilera suggested that we bring the stewardship for our surroundings a little closer to home and spearheaded an initiative to clean the streets where he and the VSP team members live.

From gathering necessary materials, to organizing teams for cleaning, to publicity in the neighborhood, the event was planned entirely by the older participants themselves. The event was a huge success, as it not only demonstrates a step towards participants proactively changing their actions toward the environment, but serves as an example of participants initiating and executing a community service project while working as a team.

Thanks to all the participants, volunteers, families, and neighbors who dedicated their time to this activity. Also, much thanks goes out to Diego Figueroa of the organization Limpiando Playas for providing the bags and gloves for the activity.
