column7:
Despu√©s de un invierno largo de fr√≠o y nieve, Valpo Surf Project resumi√≥ la programaci√≥n normal de sesiones de surf durante los fines de la semana. Participantes de VSP, quienes han estado trabajando duro en sus clases de ingl√©s y nataci√≥n durante el invierno, fueron recompensados con tiempo excelente y olas buenas para el aprendizaje en sus primeras sesiones de la primavera.

Tambi√©n llevamos algunos miembros de nuestro grupo de menores (entre 8 y 11 a√±os) a la playa por la primera vez. Gracias a todos los voluntarios que nos ayudaron con las sesiones. Fue la primera vez que mucho de ellos fueron a la playa y seguramente fue la primera vez que tuvieron la oportunidad de surfear. Tambi√©n gracias a Pedro Alfonso Lopez Aros y Sandra Paola Mena O√±ate, quienes proveyeron el uso de su van para transportar los participantes durante una sesi√≥n de surf.

After a long winter of wind and cold rain, Valpo Surf Project resumed normal scheduling of weekend surf sessions at local beaches near Valpara√≠so. Program participants, who had been working hard in their English classes and swim lessons throughout the winter, were rewarded with great weather and great learning waves for their first sessions of the spring.

Also, we brought some members of our younger group of participants (between 8 and 11 years old) to the beach for the first time. For a lot of them, it was the first time they had ever been to the beach, and it was certainly the first time they had the opportunity to surf. Thanks to all the volunteers who helped out with surf sessions. Also, a special thanks to Pedro Alfonso Lopez Aros and Sandra Paola Mena O√±ate for providing the use of their van to transport VSP participants during one surf session.

column7:
El 4 de Noviembre, el Valpo Surf Project tuvo una reuni√≥n con miembros del Gobierno Municipal de Valpara√≠so para presentar los participantes de VSP con un Malet√≠n Literario--una biblioteca chica producida y distribuida por el gobierno Chileno para apoyar el aprendizaje y la alfabetizaci√≥n entre familias de menos recursos.  Los Maletines se presentaron al Valpo Surf Project por Dante Iturrieta Mendez, el Director de Desarollo Comunitario, Mauricio Perez Espinoza, el Coordinador del Sistema de Protecci√≥n Social, y Ingrid Le√≥n Rivera, La Coordinadora del Programa Jefas de Hogar.    El Valpo Surf Project quiere agradecer el Gobierno de la Municipalidad de Valpara√≠so por su apoyo para el programa y sus participantes.  Esperemos que podamos seguir trabajando con la municipalidad en el futuro.  Todas las fotos por Lindsay Steuber.           


On November 4, the Valpo Surf Project received a visit from members of the Valparaiso Municipal Government, who presented each of the VSP participants with a Malet√≠n Literario--a small home library produced and distributed by the Chilean government to encourage reading and literacy among lower income families.  The Malet√≠nes were presented to the VSP participants by Dante Iturrieta Mendez, Director of Community Development, Mauricio Perez Espinoza, Coordinator of the Social Protection System, and Ingrid Le√≥n Rivera, Coordinator of the Female Heads of Household Program.  The Valpo Surf Project extends its thanks to the Municipal Government of Valpara√≠so for their support in the program and its participants and we hope to continue to work with the city government in the future.  All photos by Lindsay Steuber.

column7:
Un grupo de 11 participantes mayores del programa , acompa√±ados por 4 voluntarios y directores del programa, participaron en una limpieza de la playa en La Boca.  Organizada por la organizaci√≥n chilena Limpiando Playas, surfista local Coni Fernandez, y la escuela de surf Chile Extremo, el evento fue un gran √©xito y el Valpo Surf Project es orgulloso por participar. Gracias a la compa√±ia Virutex por proveer las guantes y bolsas al evento.  

A group of 11 older participants from the Valpo Surf Project, accompanied by 4 volunteers and program directors, participated in a beach clean-up at local beach La Boca.  Organized by the Chilean organization Limpiando Playas, local surfer Coni Fernandez, and local surf school Escuela de Surf Chile Extremo, the event was a great success and the Valpo Surf Project is proud to have been a part.  Much thanks to the company Virutex for providing the gloves and bags for the event.

column7: From June 2 to June 14, the US directors of the Valpo Surf Project took their first west coast fundraising tour and held events in Los Angeles and San Francisco.  The trip began with a tour of the LA surf shops to talk about the project and a fundraising event at the Gilberts' in Hancock Park.  After a few days, our fundraising tour led us up the coast in our borrowed Toyota Prius through Big Sur to Santa Cruz and San Francisco, where we spread the VSP word to more shops and had a guest-bartending event in SF's Tonic Bar.  Thanks to the Molly and the Gilbert family for hosting our event in LA, Tonic for hosting our event in San Francisco, and all of our friends who helped us with places to stay and showed us the sites along the way.

column7:
Valpo Surf Project se enorgullece en presentar el trabajo realizado con la carrera de Relaciones p√∫blicas y Pastoral de DUOC UC.  Felicitaciones a todos lo que participaron en el concurso de proyectos de la semana de la carrera. Muchas gracias a todos por sus buenas ideas, motivaci√≥n y aporte a VSP. Agradecemos tambi√©n las contribuciones solidarias que esta carrera ha gestionado. Estas van en directo beneficio de familias de la comunidad del Cerro Mariposas.  El llamado entonces es a continuar y fortalecer este trabajo conjunto, que nos permita entregar un mensaje potente  sobre  acci√≥n social y solidaridad. 

The Valpo Surf Project is pleased to announce a new partnership with the Public Relations department of DuocUC, a division of Pontificada Universidad Cat√≥lica de Chile, one of the nation‚Äôs foremost universities.  Three of the VSP directors spoke at the welcoming ceremony for the incoming class of Public Relations students, to explain the organization‚Äôs mission and objectives, and encourage the students to consider the role of social responsibility and community outreach as a foundation of business practice. 

Following the welcoming ceremony, members of the DuocUC Public Relations department organized a social gathering to meet the VSP participants and generously offered a donation of much-needed school supplies to the program.  We would like to thank the volunteers for coming out to meet the kids and look forward to working with the DuocUC Public Relations department in the future.

Valpo Surf Project se enorgullece en presentar el trabajo realizado con la carrera de Relaciones p√∫blicas y Pastoral de DUOC UC.  Felicitaciones a todos lo que participaron en el concurso de proyectos de la semana de la carrera. Muchas gracias a todos por sus buenas ideas, motivaci√≥n y aporte a VSP. Agradecemos tambi√©n las contribuciones solidarias que esta carrera ha gestionado. Estas van en directo beneficio de familias de la comunidad del Cerro Mariposas.  El llamado entonces es a continuar y fortalecer este trabajo conjunto, que nos permita entregar un mensaje potente  sobre  acci√≥n social y solidaridad. 

The Valpo Surf Project is pleased to announce a new partnership with the Public Relations department of DuocUC, a division of Pontificada Universidad Cat√≥lica de Chile, one of the nation‚Äôs foremost universities.  Three of the VSP directors spoke at the welcoming ceremony for the incoming class of Public Relations students, to explain the organization‚Äôs mission and objectives, and encourage the students to consider the role of social responsibility and community outreach as a foundation of business practice. 

Following the welcoming ceremony, members of the DuocUC Public Relations department organized a social gathering to meet the VSP participants and generously offered a donation of much-needed school supplies to the program.  We would like to thank the volunteers for coming out to meet the kids and look forward to working with the DuocUC Public Relations department in the future.

column7:
This past weekend the VSP teamed up with chilesurf.cl, Escuela de Surf Chile Extremo, and Roxy to clean up La Boca Beach in Con Con.  We managed to collect 160 bags of garbage left over from the tsunami after the February 27th earthquake and loads of trash left by visitors to the beach.  Our kids were excellent ambassadors of the Valpo Surf Project.  We're very proud of the work they're doing.

Thank you so much to our volunteers Alexandria, Alvarro, Jaime, Jeanette, Tara, Mark, and Reese.

column7: Tsunami warnings were/are in effect since the series of quakes that hit around mid-day today.  Everyone is safe here, but the public transportation system and downtown are absolute chaos between the earthquakes, tsunami warnings and presidential inauguration in Valpo today. Regardless, we're off to class!

column7: The Valpo Surf Project has to give a big thank you to Mark at LIQUID DREAMS SURF SHOP for his wetsuit donation to the program.  Over half the kids in our 2010 pilot program will keep warm with wetsuits from LDS.  The support of Mark and LDS has given the VSP a major jump start for our launch in just a few short weeks. We can't say thank you enough!

column7:
En √©sta segunda sesi√≥n de Valpo Surf Project, nos dirigimos a la playa la Boca en Con Con para realizar una nueva actividad. Participaron con nosotros nuestros amigos Claudio , Aileen y Bastian , quienes son vecinos del cerro Mariposa y asisten a distintos colegios de la ciudad. Nos acompa√±aron tambi√©n el Surfista de Re√±aca Jaime Santana, la profesora de pilates/Danza Natalia Naranjo y nuestra fot√≥grafa Ariadna Ponce . La din√°mica consisti√≥ en una intensa sesi√≥n de elongaci√≥n previa, liderada por la profesora Natalia, qui√©n nos entreg√≥ todas las posturas y herramientas para hacer una buen trabajo de calentamiento previo a la actividad. Enseguida nos lanzamos al agua a disfrutar y aprovechar las buenas condiciones que presentaba el mar, poco viento, olas peque√±as y buena frecuencia. Agradecemos profundamente a todos quienes hicieron de esta actividad un √©xito.

In our 2nd surf session we returned to the familiar beaches just to the north of Valpo.  Our original participant Claudio was joined by Aileen and Bastian, all of whom are from Cerro Mariposa  but attend different schools in the city. We were joined by Re√±aca surfer Jaime Santana, pilates/dance instructor Natalia
Naranjo and photographer Ariadna Ponce. The session started off with an intense stretch/warm-up led by Natalia, who demonstrated the proper form and value of stretches to help prepare for a surf. Then we hit the surf for a fun day with almost no wind and fun sized surf. Thank you so much to all who helped make this such a great day!

Valpo Surf Project

column7:
El Domingo 8 de Noviembre VSP realiz√≥ la primera sesi√≥n de Surf en Chile, fue un encuentro donde lo principal fue la diversi√≥n , el aprendizaje y las olas. Nuestro primer participante Claudio vive en el cerro Mariposa de Valpara√≠so, tiene 15 a√±os y actualmente cursa primero medio en un colegio de la ciudad. 
Tambi√©n Compartieron con nosotros esta aventura nuestras amigas Ella, Kerry y Andrea, ciudadanas Inglesas que trabajan en Calera a trav√©s de Gap-Chile.

VSP agradece a todos quienes participaron en este encuentro. y los invitamos a estar atentos a las pr√≥ximas sesiones.
 
Sunday, November 8 the VSP had its first surf session in Chile.  Fifteen year-old Claudio, from Cerro Mariposa, was the VSP's first participant.  Program director Andres Ponce along with three other volunteers from the English school Gap Chile led the trip.  The VSP sends its thanks to everyone who participated in the excursion and looks forward to others joining for future sessions!

www.gap-chile.com

www.valposurfproject.com

column7:
We just finished screenprinting the first batch of VSP t-shirts.  Soon to be available at our fundraising events on October 24th at University of Maine Orono, November 14th in New York City and November 20th in Cambridge, Massachusetts.  Mark your calendars and save the dates.

Check back for more updates on the fundraisers, including how to buy tickets, directions to locations, and a list of artists and businesses donating items for silent auction.
